varargs string color_rainbow(string str, int offset, int bg)

DESCRIPTION
This allows you to colorize a string using standard 30 color rainbow gradient

string str - the string to color
int offset - the offset to start coloring out, can be any number, it will be normalized to the 30 selected colors
int bg - if using RGB return background color codes

LOCATION
/adm/simul_efun/interface.c

SEE ALSO
strip_colours()
color_gradient()
